# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 13, part 2: zone-center (Gamma-point) phonons of silicon from the
# dynamical matrix.
#
# Where part 1 of this tutorial (phonon.lmp) reads the phonon frequencies off
# the thermal fluctuations of a finite-temperature MD run, here we take the
# zero-temperature, harmonic route: displace each atom by a tiny amount,
# record the forces induced on every atom, and assemble the force-constant
# (dynamical) matrix by finite difference.  Diagonalizing it gives the phonon
# frequencies AT the Gamma point, from one short, deterministic calculation.
#
# Silicon has the diamond structure: an fcc lattice with a TWO-atom basis.
# We build the 2-atom PRIMITIVE cell (a triclinic rhombohedron, exactly as in
# the copper cell of part 1 but with a second basis atom at 1/4,1/4,1/4).  Two
# atoms give a 6x6 dynamical matrix and six branches: three acoustic (zero at
# Gamma) and three optical -- the optical branches are the new feature that
# the two-atom basis makes possible.  The Stillinger-Weber potential is the
# same one used for the elastic constants in Tutorial 6.

units       metal
atom_style  atomic
atom_modify map array              # dynamical_matrix needs an atom map
boundary    p p p

# --- diamond-silicon primitive cell (fcc primitive vectors, 2-atom basis) ---
variable    a0 equal 5.4309                 # SW silicon lattice constant
variable    s  equal ${a0}/sqrt(2.0)
variable    lx equal ${s}
variable    ly equal ${s}*sqrt(3.0)/2.0
variable    lz equal ${s}*sqrt(2.0/3.0)
variable    ty equal ${s}/2.0
variable    tz equal ${s}/(2.0*sqrt(3.0))

lattice     custom ${a0}                          &
            a1 0.7071068 0.0       0.0            &
            a2 0.3535534 0.6123724 0.0            &
            a3 0.3535534 0.2041241 0.5773503      &
            basis 0.0  0.0  0.0                   &
            basis 0.25 0.25 0.25
region      box prism 0 ${lx} 0 ${ly} 0 ${lz} ${ty} ${ty} ${tz} units box
create_box  1 box
create_atoms 1 box
mass        1 28.0855

pair_style  sw
pair_coeff  * * Si.sw Si
neighbor    1.0 bin

# relax to the exact stress-free geometry: finite differences need it
fix         1 all box/relax iso 0.0 vmax 0.001
minimize    1.0e-12 1.0e-12 1000 10000
unfix       1
print       "relaxed: $(atoms) atoms, pe/atom = $(pe/atoms) eV"

# --- finite-difference dynamical matrix at the Gamma point ---
# eskm: mass-weighted output in 1/fs^2, so sqrt(eigenvalue)/(2 pi) is in THz.
dynamical_matrix all eskm 1.0e-6 file dynmat.dat binary no

# Diagonalize and report the frequencies with:  python3 phonon-gamma.py
